title: Space Ape at the Cape
description: While visiting a space center, a mysterious alien egg hatches. The gang must stop this shape-shifting creature before NASA's shuttle mission is aborted.

title: Never Ape an Ape Man
description: The gang is hired by Daphne's uncle, a famous director, as extras in his latest project. But the star of the show is a real nasty ape.

title: From Bad to Worse
description: A zombie epidemic strikes in Ooo and it's Princess Bubblegum's fault.

title: Battle of the Humungonauts
description: A pair of brutal gargantuas begin breaking apart the town, which sadly mirrors the fractured relationship of Mystery Inc. See, while searching for Shaggy, Scooby accidentally discovers him canoodling with Velma. Feeling betrayed, Scooby is inconsolable despite the best efforts of Fred and Daphne to cheer him up and put the team back together. Although they ultimately reunite to capture and defeat the Humongonauts, the rift in the gang is deep and the question by the end of the episode soon becomes can Mystery Inc. ever be healed again?

title: What the Hex Is Going On?
description: When the gang visits the Weatherby estate, they must investigate a mysterious voice and a ghost who demands the family return its fortune to a neighboring clan.

title: Go West Young Scoob
description: The Mystery Inc. gang visits a robot resort for living out Western movie fantasies. Then the robots turn on the gang.

title: Haunted Campfire
description: The campers must battle ghosts of their own creation after their scary stories mysteriously come true.

title: Uncle Scooby and Antarctica
description: Scooby-Doo and the gang accompany a penguin back to its home in Antarctica and find a finned creature from the sea dragging victims to an icy fate.

title: The Secret of the Ghost Rig
description: A mysterious ghost trucker is terrorizing Crystal Cove. Add to that all the doorknobs have begun to disappear from around town, someone has hidden a priceless diamond and Fred's dad, the Mayor, is up for re-election against a guy named Avocados. Scooby and the gang have their hands full. Oh, and did we mention Daphne has been set-up on a blind date with a pinhead named Rung Ladderton, who - wait for it - sells ladders for a living.

title: The Mirror
description: When Gumball refuses to forward a scare email, the curse becomes all too real. Gumball receives a scare-email from a freaky ghost and decides to ignore it, despite Darwin's advice. He refuses to admit it, but the curse starts to come true and his whole family gets dragged into another dimension. Gumball and Darwin, with help from Carrie, set out to save their family.

title: Horror Club
description: Steven goes to the lighthouse to watch scary movies with Ronaldo, Lars and Sadie.

title: Suerte
description: When Vic cheats on an enchanted board game, the malevolent characters come to life, and it's up to V & V to figure out how to put them back in the game.

title: Safari So Goodie!
description: Daphne's video safari goes in search of disappearing African animals and gets derailed by animalistic demons.

title: The Curse
description: Gumball experiences an impossibly unfortunate chain of events.

title: Haunted House Hang-Up
description: The gang investigates a haunted southern mansion when the Mystery Machine overheats and strands them nearby.

title: The Grasp of the Gnome
description: The Royal Knights Faire has come to Crystal Cove and the whole gang is in attendance. Unfortunately, so is a scary gnome who has begun attacking and paralyzing guests. Specifically, guests who are wearing pirate costumes. The gang decides to help trap the gnome. But when Shaggy, who is dressed as a pirate along with Scooby, is captured by the frightening little beast, it quickly becomes a race against time to find him or Scooby could lose his best buddy forever.

title: Mummy Scares Best
description: The Mystery Inc. gang travels to Egypt, where a mummy is on the loose and turning everyone into Zombies on an archaeological dig.

title: The Legend of Alice May
description: There's a new girl at Crystal Cove High named Alice May and she's set her romantic sights on Fred. Only one problem, Alice is dead! That's right, Fred's new girlfriend is a dead girl. Alice is a ghost, famous for snatching up guys like Fred and disappearing with them forever. Now, she wants to take Fred to the prom, which means he's next. Fortunately, Daphne also wants to go to the prom with Fred and she's not going to let Alice beat her to the "punch" bowl (wink-wink). And what about the rest of the gang? Well, they've got problems of their own. See, Velma wants to go the prom with Shaggy but Scooby wants Shaggy to watch a Vincent Van Ghoul marathon with him. You keeping up? Good because this one is going to get nasty and when it's over, Scooby and the gang will never be the same again.

title: In Fear of the Phantom
description: Velma's favorite band, the Hex Girls, is in town and the gang has a front row seat. Unfortunately, so does an evil specter named The Phantom, who wants the Hex Girls out of the music business permanently! Solution? Send Daphne undercover as Crush, the newest member of the band. But when she's nabbed by the Phantom, Fred goes into freakout mode finally realizing he actually has feelings for Daphne. Meanwhile, Scooby and Shaggy are having their own problems due to Shaggy spending too much time with Velma. His solution: replace Shaggy with a puppet.

title: Jeepers It's the Creeper
description: The kids look for a ghostly bank robber, who seems able to walk through walls.

title: Lights, Camera, Mayhem!
description: The gang visits the set of a spy movie and encounters the ghost of a teen idol.

title: Ghost Fly
description: Jake and the tree house are haunted by a vengeful spectre.

title: A Scooby-Doo Valentine's Day
description: When Scooby-Doo and the gang return to Coolsville for Valentine's Day, they discover teenagers are being kidnapped from Lover's Lane and they are the prime suspects. To make matters worse, Shaggy learns his former girlfriend is dating JC Chasez!

title: The Ghouls
description: It's Halloween in Elmore. As the kids go trick or treating we see what everyone in town is up to. The ghosts and ghouls are finding it increasingly difficult to scare children, and are only scaring part-time. Can Gumball and Darwin help them get their scare back?

title: Monster Squad!
description: The Titans want to be the scariest trick-or-treaters in town, so Raven casts a spell to turn them into real monsters.

title: Welcome to the Underworld 2
description: After Vic loses a wrestling match, V&V journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

title: Monster Visit
description: The monsters get nervous when their Godmonster comes for a visit.

title: The Dragon's Secret
description: After an exchange student named Mai Lee shows up in town to stay with Velma, strange Kung Fu wizards begin attacking the town trying to get her.

title: Terror Tales of the Park VI
description: In Regular Show's sixth installment of "Terror Tales," the guys gather in the house on the Dome and tell scary Halloween stories just like ol' times, only this Halloween, the stories have an extra terrifying, science fiction twist.

title: It's Mean, It's Green, It's the Mystery Machine
description: When the Mystery Machine comes to life and beings driving by itself, the gang tries to find the clues, which leads them to The Mystery Kids, the band who formerly owned the Mystery Machine.

title: Ready to Scare
description: The gang goes to Paris to see Daphne's cousin become model of the year. But they find she's been abducted by a giant gargoyle.

title: Nightmare Hospital
description: Steven and Connie sneak into a hospital to recover Rose's Sword.

title: The Poltergeist
description: Gumball and Darwin give Mr Robinson a home and end up saving his marriage.

title: The Creeps
description: Finn & Jake receive an invitation to a masquerade dinner banquet from Count Creepystein.

title: A Clue for Scooby-Doo
description: Scooby and the gang become mixed up in a mystery when he surfs into what appears to be the ghost of Captain Cutler.

title: NinjaGo: Masters of Spinjitzu - Day of the Departed
description: When Cole returns to Yang's haunted temple to seek revenge on the former Airjitzu Master who turned him into a ghost, he accidentally uses a powerful Dark Magic blade that unleashes the spectral forms of Ninjago's greatest villains and traps himself in the temple! While Cole battles for his freedom, the Ninja must return their ghostly foes to the Departed Realm before they gain the power to remain in Ninjago forever!

title: When the Cicada Calls
description: Bugs are taking over Crystal Cove and attacking some of its most prominent citizens. With Mystery Inc. back together as a team, they begin to investigate and discover all of the attacks have been on employees of a company called Destroido that makes Shaggy and Scooby's favorite snack food - Granma Moonbeams Nature Slivers. Somebody or something wants the company shut down. But when the gang gets too close to the truth, they become the bug's newest target. Of course, the timing couldn't be worse because this just happens to be the moment Fred has decided to make his move on Daphne and finally ask her out. That ain't gonna happen, though, if there are a bunch of bugs trying to kill them.

title: Large Dragon at Large
description: The gang attends a Renaissance Faire, where a dragon interrupts their fun!

title: All Fear the Freak
description: The mystery comes to a close. The Scooby gang finally gets to the bottom of what happened to the original Mystery Incorporated and why they disappeared.

title: Riva Ras Regas
description: A big star's debut concert in new Las Vegas is sabotaged by a ghost from old Las Vegas.

title: Escape from Mystery Manor
description: The gang investigates the disappearance of the original Mystery Inc. gang.

title: Scooby-Doo and a Mummy, Too
description: The gang helps a professor set up an ancient Egypt exhibit but the star of the display keeps vanishing.

title: Frybo
description: Steven helps a Boardie kid with his grueling job by using a magical gem shard that can bring clothing to life.

title: Ghosthaste
description: Vambre becomes enamored of a poltergeist within Ghost Magisword and Prohyas must save her before his sister becomes a ghost herself!

title: Simple Plan and the Invisible Madman
description: While traveling to the Montreal Rock Festival, Scooby and company rescue the band Simple Plan from an invisible madman.

title: Trick or Threat
description: Four kids in Justice League costumes are trick or treating on Halloween when they investigate a spooky house. As dangers befalls them inside, they come to realize that maybe they're not kids at all, but real Justice Leaguers under a spell.

title: Pompeii & Circumstance
description: The gang's Italian vacation is interrupted by misdeeds in the ancient city of Pompeii, leading to an ominous visit into the mouth of the maybe not-so-dormant volcano Vesuvius.

title: There's No Creature Like Snow Creature
description: The gang travels to a mountain resort in Tibet to watch a snowboarding competition. They end up investigating rumors of a snow creature that is attacking the participants.

title: A Scooby-Doo Christmas
description: The gang gets stranded in a town where a headless snowman is on the loose and Christmas isn't celebrated.

title: The Siren's Song
description: Velma is feeling like a fifth wheel. Fred has Daphne and Shaggy has Scooby. Who does she have?

title: Computer Vampire
description: Oscar finds a mysterious old video game in the library.

title: Stakes Part 7: Checkmate
description: On the eve of battle, Marceline's archenemy comes to her with a strange proposal.

title: Farmed and Dangerous
description: The gang goes to visit the Secret Six Puppies but soon discover a mysterious demon farmer haunts their farmhouse, which was built over an ancient graveyard, and wants the puppies gone.

title: Bedlam in the Big Top
description: A ghost clown haunts a small circus, using hypnotism to bend locals to his will.

title: She Sees Sea Monsters at the Sea Shore
description: The gang's tropical island vacation gets ruined when they stumble across a boat-smashing sea monster. The terrifying ocean creature, Notto Mori, is reputedly known as the spirit of the island.

title: Recipe for Disaster
description: After Shaggy wins a trip to the Scooby Snack Factory, the gang prepare for a well deserved holiday. Unfortunately, the ghost of a former employee is lurking in the shadows!

title: Charlie's Halloween Thing 2
description: Charlie tells some scary stories featuring the Bears and their friends.

title: Gold Paw
description: The gang goes to Fort Knox Army Base to visit the secret six puppies and encounters a solid gold ghoul!

title: Lonely Haunts Club
description: Instead of celebrating Valentine's Day, Vic & Val take on a dare to explore a haunted mansion with their rivals, Charlene & Pineapple.

title: The Skull
description: Gumball and Darwin make friends with classmate Clayton, a compulsive liar who can shape-change!

title: The Song of Mystery
description: A hideous creature named Que Horrifico is turning the children of Crystal Cove in to monsters. The adults in the town are in shock, reacting in the only way they know how, by abandoning their children and running away like cowards. Only Scooby and the gang stay behind to solve the mystery. Going undercover as a family - "Dad" Fred, "Mom" Daphne, "Grandma" Velma, "Son" Shaggy and "Baby" Scooby - the gang rents a house in order to capture Que Horrifico. But when their plan backfires and Que Horrifico uses his power over the monster children to cause them to attack the gang, it looks like all is lost. That is until a cartoon character named Broccoli Head comes to their rescue.

title: Stakes Part 8: The Dark Cloud
description: The final confrontation! Who will survive?

title: Mystery Mask Mix-Up
description: When Daphne innocently buys a mask that once belonged to an ancient warlord, the gang finds itself pursued by zombies and ghosts.

title: Where Walks Aphrodite
description: Love has come to Crystal Cove. Love in the form of an evil woman by the name of Aphrodite.

title: Pawn of Shadows
description: The Scooby gang is getting close to finally unraveling what happened to the original Mystery Incorporated kids.

title: Big Appetite in Little Tokyo
description: The gang travels to Tokyo, Japan. A mystical person zaps a pizza with a monster-transformation spell and Shaggy eats the pizza! He starts to grow into a Godzilla-like monster whenever he goes to sleep and he starts eating everything in sight.

title: The Monster
description: Lumpy Space Princess's parents have come to ask Finn and Jake to find their daughter and convince her to come home.

title: Mine Your Own Business
description: The gang explores a mining town and investigate a phantom miner, who's driving the business away from a nearby dude ranch.

title: Night Fright
description: Scooby and Shaggy win a dinner date with their hero, Vincent Van Ghoul.

title: Attack of the Headless Horror
description: Fred's favorite adventurer, Rick Spartan, has come to town to take over the school's biology class.

title: Monster Party
description: Enid is faced with a choice when her old friends from Ghoul School show up.

title: Web Weirdos
description: When Finn gets trapped in a giant spider web, he ends up playing marriage counselor to a couple of grumpy arachnids.

title: Charlie's Halloween Thing
description: Charlie hosts an evening of spooky stories starring the Bears.

title: The Fast and the Wormious
description: In Mexico, the gang tries to stop a giant sand worm from wreaking havoc on the Enduro Slam 5000 off-road race.

title: Beware the Beast from Below
description: Crystal Cove may be the most haunted town in the world but that doesn't stop Scooby and the gang from trying to prove that most of its most famous tourist attractions were fakes, much to the anger and dwindling profits of their parents. But when a radioactive barrel is accidentally opened releasing a hideous sewer beast that cocoons its victims in frozen yogurt, their mystery-solving skills are put to the test. After all, what could a sewer beast, a delicious edible dessert, underground caves and shrimping boats made of balloons possibly have in common? I'll give you a little hint - the local bank.

title: Gentlemen Start Your Monsters
description: The gang goes to a champion stock car race and finds a pit stop with mayhem!

title: Decoy for a Dognapper
description: Scooby impersonates a prize-winning Great Dane to catch whoever is stealing show dogs.

title: The Secret Serum
description: There's a vampire loose in the town terrorizing the residents and stealing an odd assortment of loot. When the gang does some sniffing around, they discover an unlikely suspect - Daphne's mother. Things are already strained within Mystery Inc. and with this latest blow, the gang is truly torn in half. Girls on one side, boys on the other. Although they solve the mystery in the end, the rift in Mystery Inc. is now complete. They are a team no more.

title: King of the Zombeez
description: Frostferatu hires the Warriors to rid his castle of Zombeez when Neddy and a power mad zombie-bee queen take over.

title: Sky Witch
description: Marceline is on a top-secret mission tracking Maja the Sky Witch. But when she loses the witch's trail, Marceline turns to Princess Bubblegum for help.

title: Cat Fingers
description: Steven attempts to master the power of shape shifting, but can only shape shift his fingers into tiny cat heads.

title: Fright House of a Light House
description: Residents of a small Midwestern town are frightened when an abandoned lighthouse is haunted.

title: A Scooby-Doo Halloween
description: The gang visits Velma's relatives during a Halloween festival headlined by Kiss but the festivities are interrupted by the ghost of the town's founder and a bevy of living scarecrows.

title: The Backstage Rage
description: A sinister puppet master manipulates the gang's investigation of a case of counterfeit.

title: Spooky Boo
description: After Clarence leads a few neighborhood kids through his homemade haunted house, Chelsea suggests they go to the high school kids haunted house for some real scares. When the gang makes a wrong turn they find themselves in a mysterious house on a hill full of creepy sounds, ghoulish shadows and mutant rat men!

title: The Creeping Creatures
description: A long time ago, there was a town called Gatorburg, where gators flowed wild and free and people got rich. Now, it's a ghost town. Gators are all dried up. But when Scooby and the gang receive an imitation Gatorburg purse, they decide to see for themselves if the gators really are gone. Forced to stay overnight when someone steals the engine to the Mystery Machine, they soon discover that gators have indeed returned - only these have comb-overs, walk on two legs and don't like visitors.

title: Camp Comeoniwannascareya
description: Shaggy and Scooby-Doo are camp counselors when a ghost story comes to life!

title: A Terrifying Round with a Menacing Clown
description: Shaggy competes in a mini golf tournament that is terrorized by a giant metallic clown.

title: Foul Play in Funland
description: The gang investigates a haunted seaside amusement park.

title: Revenge of the Man Crab
description: While hosting a volleyball tournament for Trickell's Triquid diet moisture, a smooth drinking beverage just like water except not so fatty, Crystal Cove beach finds itself attacked by a hideous man crab, who has taken a liking to the tournament's female players. Desperate to stop this beast before it scares away all the tourists, the gang investigates convinced it is a disgruntled local named Skipper Shelton, famous for his delicious clam filled waffle cones, his missing nose and his hatred for Crystal Cove bureaucrats. But when Daphne is captured by the Man Crab, Scooby and the gang have to put the mystery solving into overdrive or risk losing not only Daphne but the sanity of their leader Fred, who is not taking the abduction well.

title: A Night of Fright Is No Delight
description: Scooby must spend the night in a haunted house in order to receive an inheritance.

title: A Nightmare on Aberdale Street: Balance's Revenge
description: In this Halloween adventure, Clarence uses a special jack-o-lantern to enter the world of people's dreams. He discovers that something mysterious is causing his friends to have nightmares, and Clarence needs to stop it!

title: What a Night for a Knight
description: Scooby-Doo and Shaggy stumble across a lone suit of black armor and embark on a quest to find the artifact's missing owner.

title: Stakes Part 2: Everything Stays
description: As the sun rises on her last day, Marceline recalls her long extraordinary life.

title: That's Snow Ghost
description: A ski trip turns spooky for the gang when they run into the ghostly Yeti Beast and a Tibetan hermit, who says he is responsible for summoning the monster.

title: New Mexico, Old Monster
description: The gang travels to New Mexico and finds a giant, ancient legendary bird that carries the locals off to its mysterious lair.

title: Terror Tales of the Park V
description: The fifth installment of Terror Tales finds Benson trying to spice up the park's annual Halloween party by renting a wish making machine.

title: Welcome to the Underworld 1
description: After Vic loses a wrestling match, V&V journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

title: Howl of the Fright Hound
description: After a horrible, mechanized beast begins attacking the town, all fingers begin pointing at Scooby. Before the gang can clear his name, the Sheriff has Scooby hauled away to the Crystal Cove Hospital for Criminally Insane Animals. Now, it's up to the gang to clear Scooby's good name. But standing in their way is a new enemy they hadn't counted on: a diabolical parrot named Professor Pericles, who knows more about Mystery Inc. than he should. Add to this the growing friction between Shaggy, Velma and Scooby, and you have a recipe for disaster.

title: Octi Evil/Geshundfight
description: Octi Evil: The heinous Him toys with Bubbles' mind by speaking to her through Octi, her favorite stuffed animal. Following Him's orders, Bubbles picks a fight with her sisters that lands them all in a time-out./Geshundfight: The Amoeba Boys' ill-conceived plan to stand in Townsville Park all night in the rain leaves them with a nasty virus that's really something to sneeze at.

title: Halloween
description: Carrie takes Gumball, Darwin and Anais to a real haunted house party on Halloween!

title: A Gaggle of Galloping Ghosts
description: The gang visits Franken Castle, which seems to be crowded with famous inhabitants Dracula, the Monster and Wolf Man.

title: Mystery Solvers Club State Finals
description: The Mystery Inc. gang has been invited to compete in the annual Teen Mystery Solver's Convention.

title: Wrestle Maniacs
description: When the Coolsville Wrestling Federation seems to be haunted, Carol Colossal calls on Shaggy and company for help. Scooby-Doo and his pals prove they're skills in a ghostly match.

title: A Haunting in Crystal Cove
description: Mayor Jones is under attack by a poltergeist in his own home and the only ones who can help him are the Scooby gang.

title: The Ghost
description: Gumball must learn to say "no" when Carrie the Ghost uses his body against his will.

title: 3-D Struction
description: A giant dinosaur, El Oloroso, comes to life and rampages through a museum in Central America.

title: E-Scream
description: Videogame characters come to life and menace the Mystery Inc. gang while they attend a gaming convention.

title: Hassle in the Castle
description: The sleuths shipwreck on a deserted island and explore a haunted castle.

title: Menace of the Manticore
description: After the Mayor purchases a haunted temple off the internet, Crystal Cove's only theme park, Creepy Spooky Terror Land, is besieged by a Manticore.

title: The Wild Brood
description: A rowdy Orc Biker Gang has decided to roll through Crystal Cove and no one is very happy about it.

title: Scooby's Night with a Frozen Fright
description: Shaggy and Scooby hook a frozen caveman and present the chilly artifact to Oceanland. But the creature is mysteriously thawed out and goes on a rampage.

title: Dead Justice
description: There's a new lawman in town and his name is Dead Justice, an undead cowboy sheriff who used to patrol the streets of Crystal Cove.

title: Block Long Hong Kong Terror
description: The gang's in Hong Kong when a festive fake dragon comes to life and rampages!

title: Reef Grief
description: The gang goes to Australia's Great Barrier Reef so Shaggy and Scooby-Doo can compete in a sand-castle contest. There, they find a coral creature and disappearing teenagers!

title: It Came From The Nightosphere
description: Against Marceline's wishes, Finn conjures her father, the Lord of Evil, and attempts to reconcile their rocky relationship. But when the Lord of Evil discovers his daughter has turned the family axe into a bass guitar, he takes it from her and starts sucking up all the souls in Ooo!  Now, Finn must find a way to stop the Lord of Evil and get Marceline's guitar back.

title: Chille Tid
description: Steven and the Crystal Gems try to relax with a slumber party.

title: Big Scare in the Big Easy
description: The ghosts of two rival Civil War soldiers haunt a New Orleans necropolis.

title: Scary Tales
description: During the gang's Halloween party, Unikitty discovers Brick isn't scared of anything! To get him in the holiday spirit, the gang tell their own ideas of what a spooky story is, hoping to scare the emotionless Rick for once, with each tale even scarier (and sillier) than the last!

title: San Fran-Psycho
description: While attending the Grind Games, the gang runs into the ghost of an Alcatraz prisoner, who is targeting members of the competition.

title: The Unnatural
description: The spectre of a famous ballplayer appears to stop a current home run hitting star from breaking his record.

title: Los Cadejos
description: Val holds a grudge against Vic, unwittingly attracting an evil cadejo, a mythological wolf-like beast.

title: It's All Greek to Scooby
description: A medallion Shaggy wears apparently causes an ancient myth to come to life as the Mystery Inc. gang travels in Greece.

title: Roller Ghoster Ride!
description: An amusement park full of extreme rides is haunted by the Roller Ghoster, a speed-happy spectre who frightens patrons off the thrill rides.

title: Homeward Hound
description: The secret six puppies are dognapped from the dog show, and it's up to Scooby-Doo and the gang to rescue them.

title: Ghost the Boy
description: Oscar and Hedgehog befriend a ghost who can't remember who he is.

title: Diamonds Are a Ghoul's Best Friend
description: The ghost of a Russian hockey player shows up to ruin the international world cup hockey event.

title: Who's Afraid of the Big Bad Werewolf
description: The gang goes camping and stumbles across a lonely graveyard and an empty tomb, whose missing inhabitant was suspected of being a werewolf.

title: The Shrieking Madness
description: With Mystery Inc. broken up, the gang decides to check out life after high school and spend a weekend at Darrow College. But things don't go as planned when a creature called Char Gar Gothakon begins terrorizing the campus. Turns out, this beast is a fictional character come to life. A creation of the author H.P. Hatecraft, who is a professor at the school. Although one of the other professors, Harlan Ellison, claims Hatecraft is a fraud, the creature is definitely real. And when it attacks and carries off Hatecraft to his doom, the gang realizes it has to come together once again to solve this mystery and save Hatecraft's life.

title: High-Tech House of the Future
description: The Mystery Inc. gang gets trapped in an automated house of the future that goes berserk.

title: The Scam
description: At Halloween show and tell, the class isn't buying Gumball's story about Gargaroth the Devourer until Carrie fakes a terrifying haunting. The kids convince the school to hire them as ghost exterminators and take their payment in Halloween candy. But when it turns out Gargaroth is real, suddenly Gumball is expected to be the town's savior.

title: Go Away Ghost Ship
description: The gang sets out to solve the mystery of a ghostly pirate seemingly bent on avenging his capture by a shipping magnate's ancestor.

title: Which Witch Is Which?
description: A zombie walks in front of the Mystery Machine as the gang heads into the bayou for a fishing trip, leading to a real witch hunt.

title: Spooky Space Kook
description: The gang stumbles across a UFO's landing site when the Mystery Machine runs out of gas on a deserted road.

title: Don't Fool with a Phantom
description: A phantom interrupts Shaggy and Scooby's performance on a TV dance show.

title: Spoooooky Game
description: The gang's weekly board game night has been getting a little too competitive lately, so when Unikitty finds a spooky old board game that's clearly haunted, their desire to win gets turned upside down, but cursed or not, they'll be the first to the finish line!

title: Vampire Strikes Back
description: While visiting the hex girls at a Transylvania Castle, the gang runs into a real-life vampire.

title: Daddy's Little Monster
description: Finn & Jake return to the Nightosphere to rescue Marceline and get to the bottom of what's making her act so crazy.

title: Nowhere to Hyde
description: The gang follows a mysterious figure through a marsh to the house of a latter-day Dr. Jekyll, whose alter ego is apparently a jewel thief.

title: Toy Scary Boo
description: Toys come to life in the local shopping mall, and the gang stays overnight to investigate.

title: Boogie Frights/Abracadaver
description: Boogie Frights: The Boogie Man creates perpetual night by launching a huge disco ball to block out the sun. While evil creatures are dancing and destroying in the dark, the Powerpuff Girls plot to crash the ball./Abracadaver: Al Lusion, the old-time Townsville magician, pulls off his greatest stunt yet when he comes back from the dead as the zombie Abracadaver to haunt Townsville.
